snippet.textDisplay:
In 2022, we have so many arsenal in our stockpiles such as vaccine, medicine, treatments, PPEs, equipments.

Today situation is nothing like what it was in 2020 when PPEs were scarce, vaccine was non-existent, medical equipment was in high demand. Even we now have home-kit test for covid.

I personally dont see why we need to continue this pandemic phase. The most sensible way is we go to endemic phase, then when there is variant of concern, we would increase it a bit to controlled outbreaks.

snippet.textDisplay: Still 1500+ dying here a day in the US from Covid-19. It seems premature. I have lung disease, but haven't been able to see my pulmonologist since October thanks to Delta and Omicron. As soon as non-Covid patients also can make appointments with their doctors, maybe it will feel more epidemic and less pandemic. I could always see my doctors within a month during flu seasons.
